# Pump TMA — Project Skills

## UI/UX priority (this repo)

**Apply on every UI prompt automatically** — user should not need to repeat ui-ux-pro-max, design-system, or logo/symbol rules.

When skills conflict, follow this order:

1. **`pump-tma-design-system`** — tokens, nav, typography, fintech dark/light (source of truth)
2. **`pump-tma-ui-ux`** — component classes, pages, trading patterns in `apps/web/src/`
3. **`ui-ux-pro-max`** — UX checklist + reasoning via search script; **then** read `.cursor/design-system/MASTER.md` and page overrides
4. **Ignore for Pump UI:** shadcn/MUI, generic palettes, bento/block action cards from skill output

**Never** replace Pump `pump-*` tokens or `globals.css` component classes with ui-ux-pro-max generated colors/fonts unless the user explicitly asks for a full rebrand.

### ui-ux-pro-max workflow (Pump)

1. Read `.cursor/design-system/MASTER.md` (+ `pages/<page>.md` if exists)
2. Run **domain ux/chart** searches first for components (touch, loading, charts)
3. Use `--design-system --density 8 --motion 3` only for tone research — map to Pump tokens
4. Implement using existing `portfolio-*` / `panel-surface` / `PumpIcon` patterns

```powershell
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "touch target icon button row 44px" --domain ux
python .cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "fintech trading terminal dark" --design-system --density 8 --motion 3 -p "Pump" -f markdown
```

Persisted page specs: `.cursor/design-system/pages/portfolio.md` (wallet actions, Launched=Holdings grid, Earnings cards).

### Persistent UI conventions (always)

| Rule | Implementation |
|------|----------------|
| User avatars | Circle only (`UserAvatarForAddress`) |
| Token / chain logos | Square tile — `TokenAvatar` default `shape="rounded"`, `NativeLogo` |
| Token symbols in UI | No leading `$` — display `symbol` as stored |
| Portfolio Launched tab | Same grid as Holdings: Coin · Amount · Value/PNL (mobile); + Entry · P/L (desktop) |
| Portfolio Earnings tab | `PortfolioEarningsCard` — title, description, Available (hero), Claimed, Claim CTA |

